  "formulaSource": "Rafter length via Pythagorean theorem: length = sqrt(run² + rise²). Run = half building span minus half ridge board thickness. Rise = run × (pitch / 12). Cut angles via inverse tangent. Lumber sizing per standard dimensional lumber lengths (8–24 ft). Birdsmouth cut guidance per American Wood Council and IRC Section R802.6.",
